# Files Claude Code's search/read tools should skip. Goal: keep Glob/Grep/Read
# from pulling generated, vendored, or large binary noise into context — which
# is the quiet token sink (e.g. a broad grep returning hundreds of generated
# protobuf files). This does NOT change the build or git; it only narrows what
# the agent reads by default.

# --- Generated / vendored code that IS tracked in git (gitignore misses these) ---
# 203 generated protobuf message classes — never hand-edited, pure noise in search.
packages/ibkr/src/protobuf/
# Vendored IBKR reference source/samples (Java/C++), kept for reference only.
packages/ibkr/ref/

# --- Lockfiles & maps (huge, never need to be read) ---
pnpm-lock.yaml
*.map
*.tsbuildinfo

# --- Build outputs & caches (also gitignored; listed so non-git-aware tools skip too) ---
node_modules/
dist/
.turbo/
coverage/
.vercel/

# --- Runtime state & logs (can contain large dumps; data/ may hold sensitive state) ---
data/
logs/
*.log

# --- Secrets / env (defense in depth — never surface these in search) ---
.env
.env.*
sealing.key
